(Server Room Monitoring Dashboard - Beginner Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Big Picture) Tj
T*
(Your project is a full stack application with two parts:) Tj
T*
(- Backend: Django + Django REST Framework) Tj
T*
(- Frontend: React + Recharts) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The idea is simple:) Tj
T*
(A sensor reading is stored in Django, Django exposes it as JSON through an API, and) Tj
T*
(React reads that JSON to draw charts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Flow:) Tj
T*
(Sensor -> Django Model -> Database -> DRF API -> React -> Recharts Chart) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Think of it like a server room with a wall display:) Tj
T*
(- The sensor measures temperature and humidity.) Tj
T*
(- Django is the office worker that stores the readings.) Tj
T*
(- The database is the filing cabinet.) Tj
T*
(- The API is the translator that turns records into JSON.) Tj
T*
(- React is the dashboard screen.) Tj
T*
(- Recharts is the pen that draws the graphs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Django Backend) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(models.py) Tj
T*
(Your SensorData model represents one reading from the server room.) Tj
T*
(It stores:) Tj
T*
(- temperature) Tj
T*
(- humidity) Tj
T*
(- created_at) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters:) Tj
T*
(Each row in the database is one sensor snapshot. If the sensor sends a new value every) Tj
T*
(minute, Django can save one new SensorData row every minute.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important fields:) Tj
T*
(- DecimalField is used for temperature and humidity because measurements often need) Tj
T*
(  decimals.) Tj
T*
(- created_at uses auto_now_add=True, which means Django stores the creation time) Tj
T*
(  automatically.) Tj
T*
(- db_index=True helps time-based sorting and searching become faster.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The Meta ordering = ["-created_at"] means the newest reading comes first by default.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(serializers.py) Tj
T*
(The serializer converts Django model objects into JSON.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why we use it:) Tj
T*
(Python objects cannot be sent directly to the browser in a useful way. React needs JSON,) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
