(7. Recharts draws the chart.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Short version:) Tj
T*
(Database -> Model -> Serializer -> API -> React -> Chart) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. React Frontend) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Dashboard.jsx) Tj
T*
(This is the main page logic for your dashboard.) Tj
T*
(It prepares the chart data, calculates the latest values, and sends data to child) Tj
T*
(components like SensorChart.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Right now your dashboard is using mock data, not live backend data.) Tj
T*
(That is okay for testing because it lets the charts display even when the backend is not) Tj
T*
(connected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Mock data) Tj
T*
(You created a const data = [...] array with 20 points.) Tj
T*
(Each point has:) Tj
T*
(- time) Tj
T*
(- temperature) Tj
T*
(- humidity) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This array is used as the starting chart state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(useState) Tj
T*
(React useState stores values that can change over time.) Tj
T*
(In your dashboard:) Tj
T*
(- chartData stores the list of points shown in the charts.) Tj
T*
(- lastUpdated stores the timestamp of the latest update.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When state changes, React re-renders the component.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(useEffect) Tj
T*
(React useEffect runs side effects such as timers or API calls.) Tj
T*
(In your current dashboard, useEffect starts a timer with setInterval.) Tj
T*
(Every 3 seconds it:) Tj
T*
(- builds a new mock sensor point) Tj
T*
(- adds it to the chart data) Tj
T*
(- removes the oldest point so the list stays at 20 items) Tj
T*
(- updates the lastUpdated time) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(That creates the feeling of live sensor updates.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How Recharts uses the data) Tj
T*
(SensorChart receives props like:) Tj
T*
(- data) Tj
T*
(- dataKey) Tj
T*
(- color) Tj
ET
