(- unit) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Inside SensorChart:) Tj
T*
(- <LineChart data={data}> means use the array as the chart source.) Tj
T*
(- <XAxis dataKey="time" /> uses the time field for the horizontal axis.) Tj
T*
(- <Line dataKey="temperature" /> draws the temperature values.) Tj
T*
(- <Line dataKey="humidity" /> draws the humidity values.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is why one array can power two charts.) Tj
T*
(Each object contains both temperature and humidity, and each chart reads a different) Tj
T*
(property.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How cards show values) Tj
T*
(The dashboard also takes the latest point:) Tj
T*
(- latestPoint.temperature) Tj
T*
(- latestPoint.humidity) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Those are shown in the summary cards so the number cards and the charts are based on the) Tj
T*
(same source of truth.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. How React Connects to Django) Tj
T*
(You also have a fetch helper in sensorApi.js.) Tj
T*
(Its job is to call:) Tj
T*
(- /api/sensor-data/) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It uses fetch\(\) to send an HTTP request.) Tj
T*
(If the response is successful, it returns response.json\(\).) Tj
T*
(That JSON can then be stored in React state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When /api/sensor-data/ is called, the full chain is:) Tj
T*
(Browser -> Django URL router -> DRF router -> SensorDataViewSet -> SensorData queryset) Tj
T*
(-> Serializer -> JSON response -> React fetch\(\) -> state update -> chart redraw) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important note about your current setup:) Tj
T*
(Right now the dashboard is in mock mode for testing, so it is not actively using) Tj
T*
(fetchSensorData.) Tj
T*
(The backend API is ready, but the current chart display is powered by local mock data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Beginner Summary) Tj
T*
(If you want to imagine the whole project simply, think of this:) Tj
T*
(- The server room sensor measures the environment.) Tj
T*
(- Django stores each reading.) Tj
T*
(- DRF turns the reading into JSON.) Tj
T*
(- React asks for the JSON.) Tj
T*
(- Recharts turns the numbers into lines.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Text flow:) Tj
T*
(Sensor -> Django -> Database -> API -> React -> Chart) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
