(7. Mistakes or Improvements) Tj
T*
(Here are the best improvements for your project:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Separate mock mode and live API mode clearly.) Tj
T*
(  Right now the backend exists, but the dashboard uses mock data. A simple USE_MOCK_DATA) Tj
T*
(flag would help.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Consider ReadOnlyModelViewSet instead of ModelViewSet.) Tj
T*
(  If the frontend only needs to read data, ReadOnlyModelViewSet is safer because it) Tj
T*
(avoids accidental create, update, or delete actions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Limit the queryset.) Tj
T*
(  Returning every row can become slow later. For charts, usually the latest 20, 50, or) Tj
T*
(100 records are enough.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Add validation.) Tj
T*
(  Prevent impossible values such as humidity above 100 or temperature far outside your) Tj
T*
(expected range.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Move mock data into a separate file.) Tj
T*
(  That keeps Dashboard.jsx cleaner and makes switching between test mode and live mode) Tj
T*
(easier.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Use polling or WebSockets for real-time updates.) Tj
T*
(  Polling every few seconds is the easiest beginner option. WebSockets are a good next) Tj
T*
(step for true live dashboards.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Add loading and error states when you reconnect the real backend.) Tj
T*
(  This makes the dashboard feel more reliable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. Architecture Diagram) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current frontend test mode:) Tj
T*
(Mock data -> useState -> SensorChart -> Recharts lines) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Backend mode:) Tj
T*
(Sensor -> Django Model -> SQLite Database -> Serializer -> /api/sensor-data/ -> React) Tj
T*
(fetch -> useState -> Recharts charts) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
